<FTL>


<!--PROMO EVENTS-->
<eventList name="BOSS_WARNING_NODE">
	<event load="BOSS_FLEETS_REBEL"/>
	<event load="BOSS_FLEETS_BOTH_FIGHT"/>
</eventList>

<event name="FEDERATION_BASE">
	<text>The Federation base in this reality is just as impressive as the one back in Universe 0. Much of the city below has been evacuated, but the capitol building, the center of operations, is still operational. If the Flagship destroys it, the Federation will be powerless and this reality will be lost.</text>
	<img back="BACK_EVENT_FEDBASE" planet="PLANET_INVISIBLE"/>
	<customFleet right="false" firing="false" autoDarkening="false">CUSTOM_FLEET_FED</customFleet>
	<customFleet right="true" firing="true" autoDarkening="false">CUSTOM_FLEET_REBEL</customFleet>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>Luckily you've arrived here before the Flagship. One of the few remaining Federation support ships patches up your hull and gives a few supplies.</text>
			<damage amount="-7"/>
			<autoReward level="LOW">stuff</autoReward>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<!-- the first time you arrive at the base, before the rebel fleet arrives -->
<event name="LAST_STAND_START">
	<text load="TEXT_LIGHTSPEED"/>
	<img back="BACKGROUND_LIGHTSPEED" planet="PLANET_INVISIBLE"/>
	<choice>
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="ATLAS_MENU"/>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="LASTSTAND_WARP">
	<loadEventList seeded="false" first="true" generate="true">
		<event name="HOEDOWN_WARP" req="prof_dylan_counter" lvl="3"/>
		<event name="LASTSTAND_WARP_REAL"/>
	</loadEventList>
</event>

<event name="LASTSTAND_WARP_REAL">
	<text>Name: Federation Capital
	Type: Friendly
	Unique: True
	Dominant Faction: The Federation
	Rebel Threat Level: !CRITICALLY HIGH!

	The Federation Capital is your final destination. Under siege by the Rebellion, to save this reality you must kill the Rebel Flagship before it destroys the Federation base.</text>
	<choice hidden="true" req="loc_laststand" lvl="1" max_group="0" blue="false">
		<text>Exit hyperspeed.</text>
		<event load="TRUE_LAST_STAND_START_EMERGENCY"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" blue="false" req="challenge_level" lvl="3" max_group="0">
		<text>Exit hyperspeed.</text>
		<event load="TRUE_LAST_STAND_START_EXTREME"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" blue="false" req="pilot" lvl="1" max_group="0">
		<text>Exit hyperspeed.</text>
		<event load="TRUE_LAST_STAND_START"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="COORDS" blue="false">
		<text>Reroute.</text>
		<event load="REROUTE_MENU_LASTSTAND"/>
	</choice>
</event>
<ship name="SHIP_LAST_STAND_START_EXTREME" auto_blueprint="MU_REBEL_PICKET_SELITE_EXIT">
	<destroyed load="LAST_STAND_START_EXTREME_FINISH"/>
	<deadCrew load="LAST_STAND_START_EXTREME_FINISH"/>
	<crew>
		<crewMember type="human_soldier" prop="0.5"/>
		<crewMember type="human_mfk" prop="0.5"/>
	</crew>
</ship>
<event name="TRUE_LAST_STAND_START_EMERGENCY">
	<metaVariable name="juke_laststand" op="set" val="1"/>
	<changeBackground>BACK_EVENT_LASTSTAND</changeBackground>
	<metaVariable name="prof_finalsector" op="add" val="1"/>
	<customFleet right="false" firing="true" autoDarkening="false">CUSTOM_FLEET_REBEL</customFleet>
	<playSound>lightspeed</playSound>
	<recallBoarders/>
	<text>It seems your impromptu departure from Node 17 has spelled disaster for the Federation. The Flagship has already reached the base and the Federation forces here are overwhelmed. There's no time to waste, you need to get to the base immediately!</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<goToFlagship atBase="true" allFleet="true"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="TRUE_LAST_STAND_START_EXTREME">
	<text>The second you exit light speed, it becomes clear something is wrong. It looks as though the entrance beacon is under attack by an MFK Ace!</text>
	<changeBackground>BACK_EVENT_LASTSTAND</changeBackground>
	<playSound>lightspeed</playSound>
	<!--<variable name="loc_laststand" op="add" val="-1"/>-->
	<customFleet right="true" firing="false" autoDarkening="false">CUSTOM_FLEET_FED</customFleet>
	<customFleet right="false" firing="true" autoDarkening="false">CUSTOM_FLEET_REBEL</customFleet>
	<!--<metaVariable name="prof_finalsector" op="add" val="1"/>-->
	<variable name="loc_protomv_drive_block" op="set" val="1"/>
	<ship load="SHIP_LAST_STAND_START_EXTREME" hostile="true"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="LAST_STAND_START_EXTREME_FINISH">
	<text>The MFK Ace has been taken care of, and you scrap the remains before carrying on. You contact the survivors of the Federation fleet, including Admiral Tully himself.</text>
	<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
	<variable name="loc_protomv_drive_block" op="set" val="0"/>
	<choice hidden="true" req="loc_laststand" lvl="1" blue="false">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="TRUE_LAST_STAND_START_EMERGENCY"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="loc_laststand" lvl="0" max_lvl="0" blue="false">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="TRUE_LAST_STAND_START"/>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="DETERGENT_WIN">
	<text>Before you can leave, you receive another hail from Tully. "Wait - is that detergent you have? Oh thank Newton, the Rebel blockade has drained us of essential supplies, and we have a surplus of uniforms to clean. It's not much, but with this, maybe we can get our troops back into shape!"</text>
	<achievement>ACH_ACC_DETERGENT</achievement>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>DETERGENT MODE COMPLETE!
			Congratulations Renegade on successfully completing DETERGENT MODE! It was a turbulent journey for certain, but you've pulled through triumphantly! The Federation shall have dirty laundry no more, thanks to you.</text>
			<playSound>victory</playSound>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="DETERGENT_WIN_TULLY">
	<text>Before you can leave, Tully brings up another subject. "Wait - is that detergent you have? Oh thank Newton, the Rebel blockade has drained us of essential supplies, and we have a surplus of uniforms to clean. It's not much, but with this, maybe we can get our troops back into shape!"</text>
	<achievement>ACH_ACC_DETERGENT</achievement>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>DETERGENT MODE COMPLETE!
			Congratulations Renegade on successfully completing DETERGENT MODE! It was a turbulent journey for certain, but you've pulled through triumphantly! The Federation shall have dirty laundry no more, thanks to you.</text>
			<playSound>victory</playSound>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="LASTSTAND_EMPTY_BEACON"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="TRUE_LAST_STAND_START">
	<text>You've finally arrived at Node 17, the Federation Capital. You've heard the stories of this conflict back in Universe 0, the reality where the Multiverse tech was discovered. Now, you're about to take a part in it. Your actions here will either save or doom this reality.</text>
	<metaVariable name="juke_laststand" op="set" val="1"/>
	<metaVariable name="prof_finalsector" op="add" val="1"/>
	<variable name="loc_laststand" op="add" val="1"/> <!-- if you somehow leave S8 after the lightspeed menu -->
	<customFleet right="false" firing="false" autoDarkening="false">CUSTOM_FLEET_FED</customFleet>
	<changeBackground>BACK_EVENT_LASTSTAND</changeBackground>
	<playSound>lightspeed</playSound>
	<choice hidden="true" req="rep_general" lvl="-2147483648" max_lvl="3" max_group="0" blue="false">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>With a quick scan of your ID, you are allowed through the beacon without issue.</text>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_MULTIVERSE" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "So you're the Multiverse ship I've heard about? You've come a long way, and I can only hope it's all paid off. You're the Federation's last stand against the Flagship."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_FLAGSHIP" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "Oh dear god, the Rebellion's sent ANOTHER Flagship? We're screwed... wait, you aren't with the Rebels. Universe 0 sent the Rebel's super weapon to destroy the super weapon? I guess it's about freaking time we fight fire with fire."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_PIRATE" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "A... pirate? I didn't know we hired mercenaries... Not that it's an issue, you're here now and you're probably the best chance we've got."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_TUCO" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "Is that... Tuco? Which one of you hired Tuco as a mercenary? Well, I appreciate your... dedication to the Federation. Let us just hope that it pays off."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_GAMBLING" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "A gambling vessel. I'm not certain where these ships are coming from, but if you're the key to defeating the Flagship, then I'm not going to complain."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_TUCO_GOLD" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "That's a very bright ship you have. I'm sure a fascinating story stands behind it. I'd love to hear it some day, assuming we aren't all dead at the end of this."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_PLEASURE" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "In all my years, I never thought the Federation's last chance, our saving grace, would fall upon... a Slug Pleasure Cruiser. I can't imagine how you stand piloting that thing. At least, it looks like you've made it combat ready enough to face the Flagship."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_GHOST" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "Woah, your ship has taken quite the beating. If I didn't know better, I would have assumed you showed up already dead. Let's hope that isn't the fate you await."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_DYNASTY" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "I thought the Dynasty was determined to avoid the Federation and let us battle to extinction with the Rebels? Has the Prime Reaper finally changed his mind and given us a second chance? Well, I'm grateful. We need all the help we can get against the Flagship."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_GHOSTHUNTER" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "I can't seem to explain it, but witnessing your ship gives me the urge to make an Old-Earth reference, but I'm afraid it would be too outdated."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_AUGMENTED" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center "A Lanius vessel? Or... whatever that is. Not sure where you got that paintjob from, but let's hope your ship is as deadly as it looks."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_ANCIENT" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "Your ship looks like the holograms I've seen of the original Multiverse drive. I hope that means you've brought the best tech you could, because you're our last line of defense."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_ENGI" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "I wasn't told we were receiving more reinforcements from the Engi. I'm glad, because our forces are almost dried up."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_ZOLTAN" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "I didn't think the Zoltans would ever show up. Glad to know they had the dedication to bring exactly one ship."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_ZOLTAN_OLD" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "What in god's name are you? I've never seen a Zoltan ship or a creature like you before... But it seems you're a better ally than the Ministry if you've actually come to help us."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_DUSKBRINGER" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "I didn't know the Federation had access to Duskbringer tech. I'm not sure how to think about this, but we have more pressing matters."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_HIVE" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "Support from the Hive? I can't say this was expected. Not that I'm complaining, we need all the help we can get against the Flagship."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_GYGES" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "Is that the Gyges? I thought that ship was destroyed in the Federation-Mantis war... I'll never get used to this Multiverse stuff."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_FREEMANTIS" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "Oh, I did not realise your ship was of Free Mantis origins. I didn't predict what valuable allies they would be, but I suppose it makes sense, with Mantis being such excellent fighters."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_ROCK" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "The Rock Elders sent a cruiser to fight for us? I can't imagine their reasoning, but you're our last chance if we want to win this fight."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_OUTCAST" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "I thought the Outcasts were indifferent to the war. Well, I'm not one to turn down the help. We need every ship we can get to take down this Flagship."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_LOSTSUN" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "I'm surprised the Lost Suns took the effort to provide any assistance. Perhaps I underestimated them as allies. I'm glad you've arrived, we're on our last leg and need all the help we can get."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_CULTIST" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "A cult? I... sure, not the strangest thing I've seen. Let's hope that massive ship of yours is ready for the Flagship, yes?"</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_CRYSTAL" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "Assistance from the Crystalline people? Not the last thing I expected, but certainly not the first either. Let us both hope your Crystal tech will stand against the Rebellion's Flagship."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_SLUG" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "Slugs? Why did it have to be Slugs... I'm sure you're here looking for a reward, and perhaps we can work out a deal afterwards. But first, we need to take out the Flagship. The Federation can't stand much more of this attack, and if you came all this way I'm certain you mean business."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_LEECH" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "I didn't realize the Eargen Republic had the resources to send in a ship to help the Federation. No less, I'm glad you're here. Let's hope those tales of the once mighty Leech military were true and we're about to see a resurgence, because we sure as hell need it."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_COALITION" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. He recoils in shock at the sight of your ship. "A Coalition vessel? This must be some joke... the only reason I can fathom receiving support from the Coalition would be our mutual enemy in the Rebellion. If so, then we can use all the help we can get, even from unlikely allies."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_ORCHID" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. He recoils in shock at the sight of your ship. "Orchids, hmmm? I didn't think your kind would take it upon yourselves to assist in this battle. I'm grateful for the reinforcements, we're running thin on soldiers and ships and every ounce of help is worth millions."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" max_group="1" req="SHIP_VAMPWEED" blue="false">
				<text>Contact Federation command.</text>
				<event>
					<text>On the vidscreen appears several Federation and Engi officers, as well as Admiral Tully in the center. "Vampweeds? I cannot say I expected any support from the Confederacy. Is all of that drama from the Federation-Mantis War finally water under the bridge? Well, I suspect not... but we can discuss this later. Right now there's a Flagship that needs killing."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="LAST_STAND_START_2"/>
					</choice>
