<event name="FLAGSHIP_JERRY">
	<text>Not too long later, Vance appears on your screen, his bright orange uniform and massive, muscular figure standing out from the faded white of the officers around him. You aren't sure where Vance is, but that no longer matters.</text>
	<variable name="loc_vance_betrayal" op="set" val="1"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>Vance stares down to look at his star nephew, a look of confusion upon his face. "Jerome? Have you been taken by this scum to be used as a mere trading good with me? How pathetic of the Federation. Do not worry nephew, I will send my finest strike force to rescue you." Jerry shakes his head. "N-no sir. I'm no hostage. I've come to bargain."</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Bargain? You aren't making any sense boy. Spit it out already. How much are the Feds demanding for your release?" Jerry shakes his head again. "I'm not a hostage Uncle. I joined these men and women on my own volition. I... I hope to end this war. Can't you see how pointless this is? We fight this endless war for what? When does it end? Ever? There's infinite universes, surely you can see how pointless this is!"</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event>
							<text>Jerry tries to continue, but Vance cuts him off. "You.. you left the protectorate? Then Cyra... Cyra... no. No, this can't be... A-and my nephew? A traitor? My own... nephew?" A tear comes to Vance's eye, but he wipes it away immediately, then turns his back to the screen. "Enough of this. If this is your decision, then so be it. You will die a short sighted fool, just as the Renegade. Goodbye, Jerome."</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Continue...</text>
								<event>
									<text>Jerry collapses to his knees, shocked and speechless as how easily he was betrayed. "I should have known..." Jerry chokes up a sob, and holds his head in his hands while tears form puddles on the ground.</text>
