				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice>
		<text>We have no need for this fuel anymore. Give them as much as we can.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You transfer your fuel to the Civilians.</text>
			<item_modify>
				<item type="fuel" min="-15" max="-15"/>
			</item_modify>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Oh my... This is so much more than we could ever need. We'll certainly be able to escape with all of this! This is why I've always supported the Federation. Just make sure you kill that Flagship so it doesn't all go to waste." The Civilians are so grateful, they give you a military grade weapon that they no longer need on their ship, as well as some scrap.</text>
					<autoReward level="HIGH">scrap_only</autoReward>
					<weapon name="RANDOM"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ignore them.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Unfortunately, you cannot risk letting go of your fuel reserves at that point. You fly away from the civilian ship and mute their call.</text>
